The paper discusses bibliometric analysis and evaluation of individual researchers in the natural and life sciences, which involves analyzing citation data. This is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and computers and society (cs.CY). However, since the focus is on analyzing citation data, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
